# AI-Native Software Engineer – 24 Hour Assignment

#### Objective

Build a lightweight AI-powered Website Audit Tool that:

1. Accepts a single URL
2. Extracts and displays key factual metrics
3. Uses AI to generate structured insights and recommendations
The goal is to evaluate how you structure AI-driven systems, not to build a production-ready
product.

## Context

EIGHT25MEDIA builds high-performing marketing websites focused on SEO, conversion
optimization, content clarity, and UX.
We are exploring internal AI tools that help us quickly evaluate webpages and identify
improvement opportunities.

## Scope

```
● Analyze a single page only
● No multi-page crawling required
● Keep the solution focused and well-scoped
```
## Requirements

## 1. Factual Metrics (Required)

Your tool must extract and clearly display key metrics such as:
● Total word count


● Heading counts (H1–H3)
● Number of CTAs (buttons or primary action links)
● Number of internal vs external links
● Number of images
● % of images missing alt text
● Meta title and meta description
These metrics must be clearly separated from AI-generated insights.

### 2. AI Insights (Required)

Using the extracted data and page content, generate a structured analysis covering:
● SEO structure
● Messaging clarity
● CTA usage
● Content depth
● Obvious UX or structural concerns
Insights must:
● Be grounded in the extracted metrics
● Be specific and non-generic
● Clearly reference the factual data

### 3. Recommendations (Required)

Provide:
● 3–5 prioritized recommendations
● Clear reasoning tied to extracted metrics
Recommendations should be actionable and concise.

## Interface

Provide one of the following:
● Deployed web app link


```
● Local web app with clear setup instructions
● CLI tool
● API endpoint returning structured output
```
## Prompt Logs (Required Deliverable)

Include prompt logs or reasoning traces that show:
● The system prompt(s) used
● The user prompt(s) were constructed
● The structured inputs sent to the model
● The raw model outputs (before formatting, if applicable)
We want visibility into how you structure and orchestrate the AI layer.
You may redact API keys or sensitive information.

## Technical Expectations

Use any stack you prefer.
We are evaluating:
● Clean separation between scraping and AI analysis
● Structured outputs
● Prompt design quality
● Engineering clarity
● Thoughtful trade-offs
Keep the solution simple and practical.

## Deliverables

1. GitHub repository
2. Deployed link or runnable instructions
3. README including:


```
○ Architecture overview
○ AI design decisions
○ Trade-offs
○ What would you improve with more time
```
4. Prompt logs/reasoning traces

## Evaluation Criteria

We are assessing:
● AI-native thinking (not just API usage)
● Ability to ground AI in structured data
● Code quality and organization
● Quality and usefulness of insights
● Practical relevance to a web agency


